  <refnamediv>
    <refname>colon</refname>
    <refpurpose> (:) colon operator</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
  Colon symbol <literal>:</literal> can be used to form implicit
  vectors. (see also <link linkend="linspace">linspace</link>,  <link linkend="logspace">logspace</link>) </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>j:k</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>is the vector <literal>[j, j+1,...,k]</literal> (empty if
   <literal>j&gt;k</literal>).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>j:d:k</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>is the vector <literal>[j, j+d, ..., j+m*d]  </literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    <para>
    The colon notation can also be used to pick out selected rows,
    columns and elements of vectors and matrices (see also <link linkend="extraction">extraction</link>,<link linkend="insertion">insertion</link>)</para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>A(:)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>is the vector of all the elements of <literal>A</literal>  regarded as a single column.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>A(:,j)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>ys the <literal>j</literal>-th column of <literal>A</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>A(j:k)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>is <literal>[A(j),A(j+1),...,A(k)]</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>A(:,j:k)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>is
  <literal>[A(:,j),A(:,j+1),...,A(:,k)] </literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>A(:)=w</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>fills the matrix <literal>A</literal> with entries of <literal>w</literal> (taken column by column if <literal>w</literal> is a matrix).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
